23/03/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- A Croatian military delegation met on Monday (22 March) with members of the NATO Political-Military Steering Committee on the Partnership for Peace programme to discuss ongoing reforms within the Croatian Army, with an eye to NATO integration. 
President Stipe Mesic, Prime Minister Ivo Sanader and Defence Minister Berislav Roncevic recently agreed on the main principles of army reform, aimed at alleviating concerns about incompatibility with NATO standards.
In other news, Mirko Galic was elected Monday as the new general director of the Croatian Radio and Television Programming Council. 
Galic, who had been the acting general director, was elected to a four-year term, overcoming rival Petar Turkovic. 
(HINA - 22/03/04)
